===南水門 (남수문)===
南水門, meaning South Floodgate, sat across the [[Suwoncheon|Suwoncheon]] at the downstream end of the city walls.  The gate was a little over a kilometre from Hwahongmun, the gate at the upstream end.  Construction began on February 28, 1794, was interrupted, but continued in November 1795, the structure being completed on March 25, 1796, but having been fully operational since completion of its basic structure on January 16 that year.  The bridge had nine arches for the water to flow beneath: two more than Hwahongmun because of increase in flow.  Above the bridge there was a large brick structure instead of the usual gatehouse, as this section of Hwaseong was one of the most vulnerable.  This took up two thirds of the space above the arches, the remaining third being the bridge.

This gate was swept away in a flood in 1846. It was restored but washed away again by a flood in 1922. During the general restoration of the Fortress in 1975, no consensus was obtained on how to rebuild the gate, and the area remained reserved in its ancient status.

The issue arose again during the rehabilitation of the entire Suwon Stream, inside and outside the Fortress, that was initiated in 2006. 
<ref>{{cite web|url=http://eng.suwon.ne.kr/notice_view.asp?seqNo=51|title=Realization of Ecological Suwon Stream|work=Human City Suwon, Notice and News|date=2011-06-28|accessdate=2013-04-25|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130703025523/http://eng.suwon.ne.kr/notice_view.asp?seqNo=51|archivedate=2013-07-03}}</ref>

Concerning Namsumun, the restoration was launched in June 2010  and the restored floodgate is 29.4m long, 5.9m wide and 9.3m high. The inauguration was 2012-6-9.
<ref name="kbsnamsumun">{{cite web|url=http://world.kbs.co.kr/english/news/news_Dm_detail.htm?No=90880|title=Floodgate of Hwaseong Fortress Restored|work=KBS World (English)|date=2012-06-09|accessdate=2013-04-25|archive-date=2016-03-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304043432/http://world.kbs.co.kr/english/news/news_Dm_detail.htm?No=90880|dead-url=no}}</ref>

